                                  To determine the structure of the tilt boundaries, different starting configurations are considered by translat-\par
                             ing grain 2 relative to grain 1, as shown in Fig. 2. The grain boundary region is defined as a 5 nm thick region\par
                             across the Z direction (with the GB in the center), extending along the periodicity of X and Y directions. The\par
                             grain boundary energy (GBE) is determined by normalizing the excess energy within the grain boundary region\par
                             by the grain boundary area. Compared to previous studies where only minimum-energy structures are chosen,\par
                             this dataset also considers DGI for high-energy metastable grain boundary structures. Figure 3 shows all chosen\par
                             GB structures and their corresponding energies as a function of misorientation angles. For each misorientation\par
                             angle, 1000 initial GB structures are generated. Among them, the ones with GB energies approximately 35 mJ/\par
                             m2 apart are chosen to evaluate interaction with dislocations. Although many GBs are considered in this work,\par
                             it is now well known that grand canonical optimization strategies32 may find structures missed by the standard\par
                             \u947? -surface approach. Such structures could be computed to augment this dataset in the future.\par
\par
                             Dislocation-grain boundary interactions. To model DGIs, an infinitely long edge dislocation dipole is generated\par
                             in Grain 1 of < 112 > STGBs using a dislocation loop algorithm developed by Dang et al.26,33. This same approach\par
                             is used to generate screw and mixed (60\u176?) dislocation dipoles in Grain 1 of < 110 > STGBs. The dipole arm is\par
                             approximately 36 nm to minimize interactions between individual dislocations. The chosen slip systems for the\par
                             edge, screw, and mixed dislocations are [110](111), [011](111) and [110](111), respectively. Since the boundary\par
                             is periodic in all three directions, there are two possible DGIs, of which only the interaction with the center GB\par
                             is analyzed and reported. The dislocation dipole is positioned in a way that the right dislocation is approximately\par
                             10 nm away from the center of the GB region to minimize any short-range interactions initially. The system with\par
                             the dislocation configuration is then equilibrated at 10 K via a Nos\u233?-Hoover style thermostat and barostat34. To\par
